Final Answer:

Here are 3 movies suitable for children under 15 that will be showing in Boston theaters until the end of next month:

1. Sonic the Hedgehog 3
   - Rating: PG
   - Last showing date in Boston: January 17, 2025
   - Brief intro: Sonic faces his greatest challenge as Dr. Robotnik returns with a powerful new ally, Shadow the Hedgehog. Sonic teams up with Tails and Knuckles to uncover secrets and thwart Robotnik's latest plan for world domination.
   - Trailer: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yXCULkRLz_s
   - Theater: AMC Boston Common 19

2. Kung Fu Panda 4
   - Rating: PG
   - Last showing date in Boston: January 15, 2025
   - Brief intro: Po is tapped to become the Spiritual Leader of the Valley of Peace and needs to find and train a new Dragon Warrior, while a wicked sorceress plans to re-summon all the master villains Po has vanquished.
   - Trailer: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_inKs4eeHiI
   - Theater: Regal Fenway & RPX

3. Paddington in Peru
   - Rating: PG
   - Last showing date in Boston: January 17, 2025
   - Brief intro: Paddington visits his Aunt Lucy at the Home for Retired Bears in Peru. Accompanied by the Brown family, their trip turns into an unexpected adventure through the Amazon rainforest and mountain peaks of Peru.
   - Trailer: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EttlnCTPSL8
   - Theater: Landmark Kendall Square Cinema

